description._content: Description: View of Old City from Mount of Olives (near Sir John Gray Hill's House). The blue lines refer to the Scheme. Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 1918 Description: View from German R.C. Convent at Damascus Gate showing close proximity of modern town to Old City Walls. The blue lines refer to the Scheme. Location: Jerusalem, Palestine Date: 1918 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/743 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
